Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.15,0:01:50.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}黑客帝国刚刚上映 Cher的歌曲Believe还是头号热单\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}"The Matrix" was released and the Cher song "Believe" was the number one hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.94,0:01:54.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA也希望能有一个大手笔\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA was hoping to have a big hit on their hands as well
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.30,0:01:58.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一个令人兴奋的新火星轨道探测器 它将会研究火星的气候\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}with an exciting new Mars Orbiter that would study the Martian climate,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.61,0:02:03.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}正如你猜的那样 它被命名为 火星气候探测器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}known as you guessed it, the Mars Climate Orbiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.04,0:02:08.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA为一些成本较低 体积较小的探测器制定了新的指导方针 用于行星间任务\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}NASA set new guidelines for some less expensive and smaller probes for interplanetary missions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.22,0:02:12.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在1994年成立了一个小型航天器技术小组后\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}after a panel on small spacecraft technology was formed in 1994.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.40,0:02:18.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些新的探测器将在1000公斤以下 并配备更多专门的科学仪器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}These new probes would be under 1000 kilograms with more focused scientific instruments
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.59,0:02:23.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而不是像多年前的那种瑞士军刀式 一锅端式的航天器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}instead of Swiss Army knife do it all style spacecraft from years prior.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.31,0:02:28.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这一新计划的第一个任务名为 火星全球勘测者 于1996年\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The first mission in this new program was called the "Mars Global Surveyor" which launched in 1996,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.23,0:02:32.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从卡纳维拉尔角太空军基地SLC-17A发射台上的Delta II发射\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}on top of a Delta II from SLC-17A Cape Canaveral Space Force Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.59,0:02:36.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或着说卡纳维拉尔角空军基地 当时它是这个名字\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}or Cape Canaveral Air Force Station, as it was known at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.07,0:02:40.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这第一个探测器将绘制出比以往更详细的火星表面图\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}This first probe would map the surface of Mars with more detail than ever before,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.52,0:02:43.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这将有助于为未来的火星登陆器铺平道路\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which would help pave the way for future Mars landers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.49,0:02:47.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}火星气候探测器是继火星全球勘测者的成功之后\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The Mars Climate Orbiter was to follow the success of the Mars Global Surveyor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.90,0:02:50.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}将携带一些仪器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and would be taking with it some of the instruments
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.04,0:02:52.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最初为火星全球勘测者设计的仪器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}that were originally designed for the Mars Global Surveyor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.39,0:02:57.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}两者将成为从轨道上研究火星的小型研究站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The two would be a mini powerhouse for studying Mars from orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.43,0:02:59.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞船宽2.1m\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The spacecraft found up being 2.1 meters wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:02.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}高1.6m 长2m\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}1.6 meters tall and two meters deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:06.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它仅重638kg\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}It would weigh only 638 kilograms
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.16,0:03:11.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这让它能够被只有四个固体火箭助推器的德尔塔II火箭发着\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}making it capable of being launched on a Delta II with only four solid rocket boosters,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.46,0:03:12.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管它的体积小\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}but despite its small way,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.76,0:03:17.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它仍然塞满了科学仪器 包括火星轨道器照相机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}it was still stuffed to the gills with scientific instruments including the Mars Orbiter Camera,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.45,0:03:21.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}火星轨道器激光测高仪 热辐射光谱仪\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the Mars Orbiter Laser Altimeter, the Thermal Emission Spectrometer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.44,0:03:23.88,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一个磁力计和电子反射计\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}a Magnetometer and electron reflectometer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.02,0:03:27.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}超稳定振荡器和火星中继信号接收器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the ultra-stable oscillator and a Mars Relay signal receiver.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.19,0:03:31.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}大声说这些仪器感觉就像我编了其中的一半\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Saying those out loud feels like I was making half of them up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.36,0:03:35.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我可能应该试着偷偷随便扯些名词写进去\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}I probably should have tried to sneak in the specs on the end line for the rotary girder
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.62,0:03:37.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}来看看你们有没有走神\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}to see if any you guys are actually paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.94,0:03:40.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}探测器有八个单组元推进器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}The vehicle had eight monoprop thrusters
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.36,0:03:43.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}每个有22N的推力 用于轨道修正\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}each with 22 Newtons of thrust for trajectory corrections
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.85,0:03:48.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}四个较小的0.9N的推进器用于姿态控制\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and four smaller 0.9 Newton thrusters for attitude control.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.61,0:03:52.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最后 它有一个较大的主引擎 莱罗斯 1B\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Lastly, it had one larger main engine a LEROS 1B
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.27,0:03:56.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为火星进入机动点火提供640N的推力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}that provided 640 Newtons of thrust for the Mars insertion burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.19,0:03:59.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}火星气候探测器有一个独特的设计\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Mars Climate Orbiter had a unique design.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.50,0:04:03.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它只有一个大的太阳能电池板位于一侧\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}It only had a single large solar panel off to one side,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.41,0:04:06.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是能够在火星产生500瓦电力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which was capable of 500 watts at Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:11.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}另一方面 因为火星比地球离太阳远50%\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}which side note because Mars is 50% further away from the Sun than the Earth is,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.13,0:04:18.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}由于平方反比定律 火星上太阳能电池板的功率约为地球上的45%\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}due to the inverse square law, a solar panel on Mars is about 45% as powerful as it is on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.78,0:04:22.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}1998年12月11日 UTC 18:45\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}On December 11th 1998, at 18:45 UTC,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.02,0:04:27.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}火星气候探测器从卡纳维拉尔角空军基地的SLC-17A发射台起飞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the Mars Climate Orbiter took off from Cape Canaveral Air Force Station SLC-17A
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.81,0:04:30.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}开始其10个月的旅程前往火星\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}beginning its 10 month journey to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.18,0:04:32.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这次发射中我最喜欢的一件事是\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}One of my favorite things about this launch is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.16,0:04:36.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Star-48B自旋稳定固体第三级\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the Star-48B spin stabilized solid propellant third stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.57,0:04:42.63,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}没错 它是自旋稳定的 所以如果在推力上有什么小的偏移\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}That's right, its spin stabilize So if there's any minor offset in the thrust,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.63,0:04:45.39,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你可以通过分级旋转来知道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}you can know it out by spinning the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.39,0:04:46.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一旦点火燃烧完毕\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Once the burn is complete,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.70,0:04:50.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有一个溜溜球式反自转机制大致知道旋转的状态\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}there's a YoYo Despin mechanism that mostly knows how the spin,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.52,0:04:54.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}正是这样的东西让我认为是如此的酷\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}it‘s stuff like this that I think is just so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.68,0:04:57.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}于是这个小探测器上路了 一切看起来都不错\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}So the little probe was on its way, everything looking good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.45,0:04:59.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}像所有的深空飞行任务那样\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}And like all deep space missions,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.41,0:05:05.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4} 一路上几次轨迹修正点火以确保瞄准目标 这是正常不过的事情\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}it's normal to do a few correction burns along the way to make sure you nail your target.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.25,0:05:08.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也不是什么大不了事 我是说 每次都是这么做的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}And that's no big deal I mean, this is done all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:12.75,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,835)\blur4}四次方向修正进行于 1998年12月21日\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}There were four course corrections performed on December 21st 1998,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.96,0:05:17.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,835)\blur4}3月4日 7月25日和1999年9月15日\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}March 4th, July 25th and September 15th 1999.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.61,0:05:23.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在火星进入机动点火开始的前一天 还计划有一次可选的方向修正\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}There was another optional course correction planned just one day prior to the Mars insertion burn,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.87,0:05:25.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但被管理团队拒绝\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}but it was denied by management
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.47,0:05:30.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为根据以往的轨道 他们认为探测器没有偏离方向\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}because they thought based on prior trajectories that the probe was on course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.53,0:05:32.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}除了方向修正\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Alongside the course corrections,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:38.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞船还进行一些所谓的角动量去饱和 或称为AMD\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}the spacecraft also perform something called angular momentum desaturations or AMDs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.81,0:05:42.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}许多航天器做到这一点 但尤其是火星气候轨探测\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Many spacecraft do this but especially the Mars Climate Orbiter,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.94,0:05:45.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为它有这样的单面太阳能电池板\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}because it had that single sided solar panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.77,0:05:50.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它的一半比另一半经历了比其他航天器更多的太阳光压\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}It experienced more solar pressure on one half of the spacecraft than the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.62,0:05:52.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对了 有趣的一点是\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}By the way, fun side note,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.19,0:05:57.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}太阳光压是无质量的光子对航天器施加压力的动量\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}solar pressure is the momentum of the massless photons exerting pressure on a spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.54,0:05:59.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而不是太阳风\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and it's not solar wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.16,0:06:07.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}太阳风是由太阳喷出的具有质量的粒子如核子和电子组成的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Solar wind is composed of particles with mass ejected by the sun like nucleons and electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.28,0:06:11.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}感谢Scott Manley和Twitter众网友帮助我澄清理解这个知识点\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Thanks to Scott Manley and the rest of space Twitter for helping clarify that for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.98,0:06:17.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好了 所以你的飞船永远轻微地在一个你不想要的方向旋转\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Okay, so your spacecraft is ever so slightly rotating in a direction you don't want.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.61,0:06:20.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而为了使飞船内帮助维持方向的反应轮\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}And in order to keep the reaction wheels inside the spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.68,0:06:24.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不至于超时工作\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}that helped maintain orientation from having to work overtime,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.54,0:06:29.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你可以进行AMD 将飞船重新设定回理想的方向\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}you can perform an AMD to reset the spacecraft back to its ideal orientation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.14,0:06:33.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}让这些反应轮开心 不至于超时工作\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}and keep those reaction wheels happy and not overworked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.75,0:06:38.88,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在 每一次航天器执行任何角动量去饱和机动\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}Now each and every single time the spacecraft performs any desaturation maneuver
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.88,0:06:39.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或任何修正点火\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50\blur4}or any correction burn,
